title: help !
description:
okay so I hate doing this but?? It would be really cool if y’all shared this or donated or commissioned me. (My art tag is just “#my art” if you would like to check out what I do!)

Right now, money in my household is very tight. To the point where we can pay rent, but not our bills. I live with my mom, younger sister, and step dad. Our only source of income is from my step dad, who has to live in a different town most of the time to work. My mom can’t get a job because she needs to take care of me and my sister and take us to appointments (I need physically therapy for my pain, talk therapy, and my sister has OT and tutoring, and that’s not counting check ups or my moms appts) and she is physically unable to. I can’t either, because of my pain issues, tight schedule and needing extra help with school (plus social events, I’m a performer and an activist).
I just want to be able to help provide for my family, and this is the easiest way for me to do it. Sharing/donating/commissions are all super helpful!!
Thank you

summary: On Tuesday, I lost a good friend. It was so unexpected & sudden. I am fine. Her family is fine. It’ll take some time to heal. ...
caption:
On Tuesday, I lost a good friend. It was so unexpected & sudden.

I am fine. Her family is fine. It’ll take some time to heal.


I’m an atheist. I don’t believe in any deities. I don’t believe in afterlife. No heaven, no hell. I don’t know what happens to our “souls” or conscience after we die. What makes us… Us.        

I like to think that our “souls” go someplace. That maybe we go back into the universe. Maybe our “souls” get recycled into other things, be it wolves or trees. Maybe we go back into our cells. I like to think that. I don’t believe it. 

It’s comforting, so comforting, to think that the person you know is still out there somewhere after they pass. That they could be following you, they’re watching you, hanging out with their loved ones too.           

It’s comforting. It helps deal with loss. I don’t believe it’s true. & I don’t think it’s… False. I just don’t know, really. Maybe dreams connect us. I don’t know. The brain is such a confusing thing. It’s confusing how we’re confused at our own bodies.         

I hope that maybe… She did find her husband. Somewhere. I hope she’s out there with all those cats she once took care of.

Comfort in the face of disbelief may be what pulls us together. The universe doesn’t care if you’re a celebrity or an ant. It treats death the same to all living things. Maybe one day we’ll find the answer. Until then. Just… Know that I’ll miss you.
